assertion_line: 83
expression: "get_subcommand_help(\"shell\")"
---
Run a bash-compatible shell with per-command sandbox enforcement

Usage: shell [OPTIONS] [ARGS]...

Arguments:
  [ARGS]...  Script path and arguments

Options:
  -c <COMMAND>             Execute a command string and exit (like bash -c)
      --cwd <CWD>          Working directory for sandbox path resolution [default: .]
      --sandbox <SANDBOX>  Default sandbox name from the policy (used when no rule-specific sandbox
                           matches)
      --debug              Print the sandbox policy matched for each command before execution
  -h, --help               Print help (see more with '--help')
